ocaml-sdl
------------------------------------------
The goal of OCamlSDL is to provide access the multimedia hardware
in the ML programming language with the help of the SDL library.
The Simple DirectMedia Layer is a generic API that provides low
level access to audio, keyboard, mouse, and display framebuffer across
multiple platforms.

Runtime requirements:
  cygwin-1.7.1-1
  libgcc1-4.3.4-3
  libSDL1.2_0-1.2.14-1
  libSDL_image1.2_0-1.2.10-1
  libSDL_mixer1.2_0-1.2.11-1
  libSDL_ttf2.0_0-2.0.9-10
  ocaml-3.11.2-1
  ocaml-lablgl-1.04-2

Build requirements:
(besides corresponding -devel packages)
  binutils-2.19.51-1
  cygport-0.9.80-1
  flexdll-0.20-1
  gcc4-core-4.3.4-3
  make-3.81-2
  ocaml-findlib-1.2.5-1

Canonical website:
  http://ocamlsdl.sourceforge.net/

Canonical download:
  http://downloads.sourceforge.net/ocamlsdl/

-------------------------------------------

Build instructions:
  unpack ocaml-sdl-0.7.2-X-src.tar.bz2
    if you use setup to install this src package, it will be
	 unpacked under /usr/src automatically
  cd /usr/src
  cygport ./ocaml-sdl-0.7.2-X.cygport all

This will create:
  /usr/src/ocaml-sdl-0.7.2-X-src.tar.bz2
  /usr/src/ocaml-sdl-0.7.2-X.tar.bz2

-------------------------------------------

Port Notes:

----- version 0.7.2-3 -----
